Kidder Peabody and Co analyst Roy Burryissued a strong buy recommendation on Pepsico Inc, citing animproved profit outlook for both domestic soft drinks andFrito-Lay snack foods.    Pepsico climbed 7/8 to 34-3/4 on 615,000 shares bymidmorning.    Burry forecast earnings of 2.00 dlrs per share in 1987 and2.30 dlrs in 1988. In 1986 the company earned 1.75 dlrs pershare. Burry previously had a sell recommendation on Pepsico."We're looking at 10 to 15 pct earnings growth for Frito-lay in1987, a trend that should continue through the decade." Reuter&#3;